President Barack Obama has proclaimed November 2013 as National Alzheimer's Disease Awareness Month in the United States. In his proclamation, he highlights the devastating effects of Alzheimer's disease and the need for continued research and support for those affected by the disease. The President mentions the Brain Research through Advancing Innovative Neurotechnologies (BRAIN) Initiative, which aims to better understand the human brain and improve treatment for disorders like Alzheimer's. He also mentions the National Plan to Address Alzheimer's Disease, which lays out a roadmap for preventing and effectively treating Alzheimer's by 2025. The President calls upon the people of the United States to learn more about Alzheimer's disease and support individuals living with the disease and their caregivers.